# ============================================================================
# Instructions for Maintainers
# ============================================================================
#
# To set up code owners:
# 1. Replace TODO comments with actual GitHub usernames (e.g., @username)
# 2. You can also use team names if you have GitHub teams set up (e.g., @org/team-name)
# 3. Patterns follow .gitignore format:
#    - * matches anything except /
#    - ** matches anything including /
#    - ? matches any single character
#    - [abc] matches any character in the set
#    - {a,b} matches either pattern
#
# Examples:
#   /build/                 @devops          # Root build directory only
#   docs/**/*.md            @doc-team        # All .md files in docs (recursive)
#   *.js                    @js-team         # All .js files anywhere
#   src/**/test/**          @qa-team         # All test directories
#
# Order matters! Later matches take precedence.
#
# Best Practices:
# - Start with broader patterns and override with specific ones
# - Keep the number of reviewers manageable (2-3 per area)
# - Document why certain files have specific owners
# - Review and update this file regularly
# - Consider using GitHub teams instead of individual users
#
# ============================================================================
